Wash_23: The secretary said there were 2,700 people in Magandafuta. The 2007 Census indicates 1578 and projected for 2019 the number of people e and 2123. The village has 3 zones: Mpinga area where 273 households live. Chambau area with 670 houses. And Headquarters area with 757 houses. Coordinates are: Lat 19 26 0.8.451; long 034 35 43.4. In the zone of the school that ee higher did not flood but the school was without cover and the annex with sticks and straw fell. Roof of the 3 residences also fell. I could not tell if there were glasses in the school before the cyclone. The day after the cyclone the population went to the center of Mutua but 3 days later they had to leave and return to the village. Rainwater from the cyclone and then floods flooded the area of most homes. Mpinga's leader is called Joao Mpinga, and Luis Zaguete's headquarters.
Health_50: Malaria
Health_52: Magandafuta is located 3 hours walking from Mutua. Dificil acesso por causa dos riachos Senbezera, Nhate e Raul. Mas ha um chines que tira areia proximo da zona Mpinga da aldeia. Nao ha creche. Ja 20 habitentes foram aa unidade sanitaria de Mutua com diarreia mas nao ee colera.
Edu_37: Aulas interrompidas desde o ciclone. A escola primaria ee da 1 a 7 classe, com 2 turnos: 1,2,3 de manha e 4,5,6,7 aa tarde
Edu_39: Escola primaria tem 4 salas de aula e 3 casas para director e professores. sao ao todo 7 professores que tambem vivem em Mutua, Dondo ou Mafambisse. Nao conseguiram dar os contactos dos professores. Aos fins de semana os professores saiem da Aldeia.
Agr_20: Perderam as culturas que ficaram acamadas com o ciclone e submersas com as cheias. Cerca de 20 agregados familiares teem cabritos mas maioria morreu de doenca por terem ficado dentro de agua. Cerca de 7 casas teem suinos que morreram quando as cobertura das casas desabou. Maioria das casas tinha galinhas mas maioria morreu porque apanharam agua e depois os moradores foram para Mutua.
Agr_21: Populacao de Magandafuta produziu arroz, miho, mandioca, amendoim, batata doce e cana doce. As culturas ficaram primeiro acamadas (eles disseram que as culturas dormiram), o grao de milho germinou, , as folhas das plantas no geral  ficaram amarelas e cairam. Cerca de metade das casas praticam a pesca nos riachos, pescam mussopo e macacana com rede e linha. Populacao estaa a consumir peixe e folhas de mandioca que restam.
Mark_21: Nao ha lojas na aldeia.  apenas 2 casas vendem sabao, oleo e outros produtos basicos. Vao a Mutua comprar alimentos e outros produtos. Custo dos produtos sao 150 Mzm por 5kg de milho em grao, 250 mzm por 5 kg de farinha de milho, 25 mzm por kg de feijao, 100 mzm por lt de oleo vegetal de cozinha, 10 mzm por pacotinho de sal.  Hoje foi a primeira assistencia em comida enviada pelo Ingc.
Shelt_13: As familias que perderam as casas vivem debaixo de redes mosqueteiras ou de fohas de alneitas em V; usam lenha para cozinhar cerca de 10 casas fabricam carvao.
CP_19: Roubo de produtos nas machambas quando tinhame esmoas casas por hibtantes ou pessoas que veem de Mutua  para deois venderem em Mutua.

Lack of rooms not enough rooms for classes. 55 classes and only 18 rooms . This situation was there before but has worsen after the cyclone because more children coming from affected areas.

 School books were damaged by floods they lack school books . They lack school bags as well lost when houses were destroyed. 

Children have not enough to eat because families lost their crops and those families have not received any food assistance. 

They have too many children and not enough latrines some of these latrines have been damaged by the cyclone. In these schools there are a lot of orphan children one of the causes is HIV, some others go to work in south africa as miners and disappear some other disappeared or were killed as part of political struggle.

 Lack of water in the school because lack of power. The school also had night classes but difficult now with no power.

Agr_20:
Combination of drought before the cyclone and wind from Idai destroyed crops just before the harvest.  Food situation is really serious more than 60 percent of people suffering from food insecurity. 

Best way to support will be to teach people how to plant seeds that can resist droughts and how to better farm land. Next harvest season is in november so not enough food till november. So people need food right now and then seeds for the future. They still have tools. Problems are lack of water, food and power. People have to walk long distances to fetch water.
